Description
==================================================================================================
SAM [Social Affinity Maps]
A feature descriptor to capture the behavioral signature of neighbouring pedestrians termed
as Social Affinity Map (SAM) [1].

OD Matrix [Origin Destination Matrix]
Forecasting destinations is often referred to as estimating Origin=Destination Matrices [1]. 
It represents the starting & ending points of all pedestrian trajectories during a time period.

OD Prior [Origin Destination Prior]
We often have restrictions in the way pedestrians can move in a scene, encoded as priors over 
origin and destination (OD) preferences. [1]

DataSet
==================================================================================================
http://www.cvg.reading.ac.uk/PETS2009/a.html


References
==================================================================================================
[1]	Socially=aware Large=scale Crowd Forecasting, Alexandre Alahi, Vignesh Ramanathan, Li Fei-Fei